						<summary>

						<p>On a mutilated stone near the well in the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It contains details of a series of grants in the course of which reference is made to Uttarāvaṇa-saṁkrānti, the deity Mēchalēśvara and the measure called <hi rend="italic">Dānachintāmaṇiya-gaḷe.</hi> The epigraph is fragmentary and its major portion is lost. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
